			<h3 ><a href="#p79938">Re: Frustrated... battery or dead roomba?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=79938&amp;sid=53e7b36b35ea6b46b92edecdde9af8ac#p79938"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=299&amp;sid=53e7b36b35ea6b46b92edecdde9af8ac">Gordon</a></strong> &raquo; July 2nd, 2010, 2:04 am </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>s_mack wrote:</cite>...  I'm not sure if its normal or not, but the charging tabs (that contact the battery when it is inserted) only show 5V.  I would have thought that would be 22V too, but I have no idea what the circuitry in between is doing so 5V may very well be the proper voltage. ...</div></blockquote>I presume you are referring to the Home Base contacts. If so, be aware that voltage is held low (and impedance high) until the HB is satisfied that a proper Roomba has contacted the HB, then it up-switches voltage and delivers charging current to the robot.</div>

			

		</div>

		
